Pervasive Games Film Festival 






 








I’ve organized these into some loose categories of my own creation.
Games:
Participants are voluntarily inside the magic circle, outcomes are uncertain, and spectators might become inadvertently involved.
Pacmanhattan: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UeruPNFi8ZI
Pacmanhattan: Control Room: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4X4mllmFhYw
I Love Bees: http://www.42entertainment.com/work/ilovebees
Uncle Roy All Around You: http://www.blasttheory.co.uk/projects/uncle-roy-all-around-you/
Can You See Me Now?: http://www.blasttheory.co.uk/projects/can-you-see-me-now/
LARP: Lightning Bolt!: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j_ekugPKqFw
Darkon Larp: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tdItduDFmEo
Civil War Reenactment: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZNK7cS2tJgg
World Without Oil: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M-hzUGFD-Gc
REXplorer: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mf7m97tF3Ls
Shelby Logan’s Run: https://youtu.be/3An0BbCeSkg
The Lost Experience: https://youtu.be/oXK8Cp9KjXE
Majestic: https://youtu.be/PcTDMYq3xCw
Cruel 2B Kind: https://youtu.be/IAhRC75vIWc
Pranks:
Uninvolved spectators are the object and subject of the experience, and the magic circle is “weaponized” in order to disrupt their daily lives. Outcomes are uncertain.
Telekinetic Coffee Shop: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VlOxlSOr3_M
Intellivator: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JofRc_qQCAs
Mutant Giant Spider Dog: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YoB8t0B4jx4
Ghost Girl in Elevator: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8E1YjIHMxAs
Star Wars Elevator Prank: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y7-1A_j3fSM
Performances:
Participants enacting somewhat known outcomes within a permeable magic circle that can incorporate spectators, but is unconcerned with their response (vs. pranks where spectator response is the whole point).
Star Wars in Real Life: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J5gCeWEGiQI
Lord of the Rings in Real Life: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIQXUgHm4c8
Frozen Grand Central Station: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jwMj3PJDxuo
Historical Precedents:
What is Fluxus?: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cGZ9OS1Oj14
How to Make a Happening: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8iCM-YIjyHE&nohtml5=False
John Cage’s 4’33”: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JTEFKFiXSx4&list=RDJTEFKFiXSx4#t=280
The ABC’s of DADA: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EqkIJ0odFxA
The Situationist International: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=STJI8ouvUh8
Pervasive Games in Popular Culture
The Last of Sheila: https://youtu.be/NPHMoDpCHU8
Midnight Madness: https://youtu.be/rKsidHYO-zY
More Midnight Madness: https://youtu.be/gLusAy-aOJY
Even More Midnight Madness: https://youtu.be/QeVejxd7_hk
The Game: https://youtu.be/0kqQNBR09Rc
The Man Who Knew Too Little: https://youtu.be/W2bMmtNRpI8
The 10th Victim: https://youtu.be/uiJ6oghRqKY
Battle Royale: https://youtu.be/N0p1t-dC7Ko
The Hunger Games: https://youtu.be/4S9a5V9ODuY
 

















